(56,1,'2026-05-20 19:05:24','2026-05-20 19:05:24','<!--\n=============================================================\nSATU WEBSITE - HOMEPAGE SLIDER\n=============================================================\nMANAGED BY: Dean IR Office, IIT Bombay\nLAST UPDATED: May 2026\nHOW THIS SLIDER WORKS:\n- Each slide is a  block\n- Each slide contains one image (your Canva poster)\n- Clicking the image takes the visitor to the related post/page\n- The slider auto-plays every 5 seconds\n- There are previous/next arrows and dot indicators\nCANVA POSTER DIMENSIONS:\n- Use 1400 x 500 pixels in Canva (Landscape format)\n- Export as PNG or JPG\n- Upload via WP Admin → Media → Add New\n- Copy the file URL from the media library\n=============================================================\nHOW TO ADD A NEW SLIDE (currently 2 slides, max 5):\n=============================================================\n1. Design your poster in Canva (1400 x 500 px)\n2. Upload it via WP Admin → Media → Add New\n3. Copy the image URL from the media library\n4. Copy the block below and paste it before the closing\n    of id=\"satuSliderTrack\":\n       <a href=\"PASTE-YOUR-POST-LINK-HERE\" target=\"_blank\">\n           <img src=\"PASTE-YOUR-IMAGE-URL-HERE\" alt=\"Brief description\">\n       </a>\n5. Also add a new dot indicator inside id=\"satuDots\":\n   Replace N with the slide number starting from 0\n   (slide 1 = 0, slide 2 = 1, slide 3 = 2, and so on)\n=============================================================\nHOW TO REMOVE A SLIDE:\n=============================================================\nDelete the entire ... block\nand remove the last  from id=\"satuDots\"\n=============================================================\nHOW TO CHANGE THE AUTO-PLAY SPEED:\n=============================================================\nAt the bottom of this file, find:\n   satuInterval = setInterval(satuNext, 5000);\nChange 5000 to any number (in milliseconds)\nExample: 3000 = 3 seconds, 7000 = 7 seconds\n=============================================================\n-->\n<style>\n.satu-slider-wrapper {\n    width: 100%;\n    overflow: hidden;\n    position: relative;\n    background: #111;\n    user-select: none;\n}\n.satu-slider-track {\n    display: flex;\n    transition: transform 0.5s ease-in-out;\n    will-change: transform;\n}\n.satu-slide {\n    min-width: 100%;\n    position: relative;\n}\n.satu-slide a {\n    display: block;\n    width: 100%;\n}\n.satu-slide img {\n    width: 100%;\n    height: auto;\n    display: block;\n    object-fit: cover;\n}\n/* ─── Arrows ─────────────────────────────────────────────── */\n.satu-arrow {\n    position: absolute;\n    top: 50%;\n    transform: translateY(-50%);\n    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.35);\n    color: #fff;\n    border: none;\n    font-size: 1.6rem;\n    padding: 10px 16px;\n    cursor: pointer;\n    z-index: 10;\n    border-radius: 3px;\n    transition: background 0.2s ease;\n    line-height: 1;\n}\n.satu-arrow:hover { background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.65); }\n.satu-arrow.prev { left: 12px; }\n.satu-arrow.next { right: 12px; }\n/* ─── Dots ───────────────────────────────────────────────── */\n.satu-dots {\n    position: absolute;\n    bottom: 10px;\n    width: 100%;\n    display: flex;\n    justify-content: center;\n    gap: 8px;\n}\n.satu-dot {\n    width: 10px;\n    height: 10px;\n    border-radius: 50%;\n    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.45);\n    cursor: pointer;\n    transition: background 0.25s ease, transform 0.25s ease;\n    display: inline-block;\n}\n.satu-dot.active {\n    background: #ffffff;\n    transform: scale(1.25);\n}\n/* ─── Mobile ─────────────────────────────────────────────── */\n@media (max-width: 600px) {\n    .satu-arrow { font-size: 1.1rem; padding: 7px 11px; }\n}\n</style>\n<!-- SLIDER HTML — Edit image URLs and links below -->\n        <!-- ==========================================\n             SLIDE 1\n             - Replace IMAGE-URL-1 with your Canva poster URL\n             - Replace POST-LINK-1 with the page/post URL\n             - Replace \"Description 1\" with a short description\n             ========================================== -->\n            <a href=\"POST-LINK-1\" target=\"_blank\">\n                <img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/hero_dummy1.png\" alt=\"Description 1\">\n            </a>\n        <!-- ==========================================\n             SLIDE 2\n             - Replace IMAGE-URL-2 with your Canva poster URL\n             - Replace POST-LINK-2 with the page/post URL\n             - Replace \"Description 2\" with a short description\n             ========================================== -->\n            <a href=\"POST-LINK-2\" target=\"_blank\">\n                <img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/hero_dummy2.png\" alt=\"Description 2\">\n            </a>\n        <!-- PASTE ADDITIONAL SLIDES HERE (max 3 more) -->\n    <button onclick=\"satuPrev()\">&#8249;</button>\n    <button onclick=\"satuNext()\">&#8250;</button>\n        <!-- ADD ONE MORE DOT HERE FOR EACH NEW SLIDE YOU ADD -->\n        <!-- Example for slide 3:  -->\n        <!-- Example for slide 4:  -->\n        <!-- Example for slide 5:  -->\n					<style>\n/* ─── Section Wrapper ────────────────────────────────────── */\n.satu-cards-section {\n    width: 100%;\n    padding: 60px 48px;\n    background-color: #ffffff;\n    display: flex;\n    justify-content: center;\n    align-items: stretch;\n    gap: 32px;\n    box-sizing: border-box;\n}\n/* ─── Individual Card ────────────────────────────────────── */\n.satu-card {\n    flex: 1;\n    max-width: 360px;\n    background-color: #ffffff;\n    border-radius: 8px;\n    border: 1px solid #e0e0e0;\n    box-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);\n    padding: 40px 32px;\n    display: flex;\n    flex-direction: column;\n    align-items: center;\n    text-align: center;\n    cursor: pointer;\n    text-decoration: none;\n    color: inherit;\n    /* Float animation setup */\n    transition: transform 0.35s ease, box-shadow 0.35s ease, border-color 0.35s ease;\n    transform: translateY(0);\n}\n.satu-card:hover {\n    transform: translateY(-10px);\n    box-shadow: 0 16px 40px rgba(107, 30, 30, 0.18);\n    border-color: #6B1E1E;\n    text-decoration: none;\n    color: inherit;\n}\n/* ─── Card Icon ──────────────────────────────────────────── */\n.satu-card-icon {\n    width: 64px;\n    height: 64px;\n    background-color: #6B1E1E;\n    border-radius: 50%;\n    display: flex;\n    align-items: center;\n    justify-content: center;\n    margin-bottom: 24px;\n    flex-shrink: 0;\n    transition: background-color 0.35s ease;\n}\n.satu-card:hover .satu-card-icon {\n    background-color: #8B2525;\n}\n.satu-card-icon svg {\n    width: 30px;\n    height: 30px;\n    fill: #ffffff;\n}\n/* ─── Card Title ─────────────────────────────────────────── */\n.satu-card-title {\n    font-family: \"Palatino Linotype\", Palatino, Georgia, serif;\n    font-size: 1.3rem;\n    font-weight: 700;\n    color: #6B1E1E;\n    margin-bottom: 14px;\n    line-height: 1.3;\n}\n/* ─── Card Description ───────────────────────────────────── */\n.satu-card-desc {\n    font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\n    font-size: 0.88rem;\n    color: #555555;\n    line-height: 1.7;\n    flex: 1;\n    margin-bottom: 24px;\n}\n/* ─── Card Button ────────────────────────────────────────── */\n.satu-card-btn {\n    display: inline-block;\n    padding: 9px 24px;\n    background-color: #6B1E1E;\n    color: #ffffff !important;\n    font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\n    font-size: 0.82rem;\n    font-weight: 600;\n    letter-spacing: 1px;\n    text-transform: uppercase;\n    text-decoration: none !important;\n    border-radius: 4px;\n    transition: background-color 0.25s ease;\n    margin-top: auto;\n}\n.satu-card:hover .satu-card-btn {\n    background-color: #8B2525;\n}\n.satu-card,\n.satu-card *,\n.satu-card:hover,\n.satu-card:hover * {\n    text-decoration: none !important;\n}\n/* ─── Tablet ─────────────────────────────────────────────── */\n@media (max-width: 900px) {\n    .satu-cards-section {\n        padding: 48px 28px;\n        gap: 24px;\n    }\n}\n/* ─── Mobile ─────────────────────────────────────────────── */\n@media (max-width: 650px) {\n    .satu-cards-section {\n        flex-direction: column;\n        align-items: center;\n        padding: 36px 20px;\n        gap: 20px;\n    }\n    .satu-card {\n        max-width: 100%;\n        width: 100%;\n        padding: 32px 24px;\n    }\n}\n</style>\n<section>\n    <!-- ── Card 1: About SATU ── -->\n    <a href=\"/about-satu/\">\n            <!-- Info / About icon -->\n            <svg viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\">\n                <path d=\"M12 2C6.48 2 2 6.48 2 12s4.48 10 10 10\n                         10-4.48 10-10S17.52 2 12 2zm1 15h-2v-6h2v6zm0-8h-2V7h2v2z\"/>\n            </svg>\n        About SATU\n            Learn about the SATU Presidents\' Forum — its vision, mission,\n            member universities across Southeast and South Asia and Taiwan,\n            and IIT Bombay\'s role in this academic alliance.\n        Learn More\n    </a>\n    <!-- ── Card 2: Activities ── -->\n    <a href=\"/activities/\">\n            <!-- Calendar / Activities icon -->\n            <svg viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\">\n                <path d=\"M19 3h-1V1h-2v2H8V1H6v2H5C3.89 3 3 3.9 3 5v14\n                         c0 1.1.89 2 2 2h14c1.1 0 2-.9 2-2V5c0-1.1-.9-2-2-2zm0\n                         16H5V8h14v11zM7 10h5v5H7z\"/>\n            </svg>\n        Activities\n            Explore SATU\'s academic exchanges, joint research initiatives,\n            webinar series, innovation competitions, and upcoming events\n            hosted by member universities.\n        Explore\n    </a>\n    <!-- ── Card 3: Previous Website ── -->\n    <a href=\"https://satu.ncku.edu.tw/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">\n            <!-- External link icon -->\n            <svg viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\">\n                <path d=\"M19 19H5V5h7V3H5a2 2 0 00-2 2v14a2 2 0\n                         002 2h14a2 2 0 002-2v-7h-2v7zM14 3v2h3.59\n                         l-9.83 9.83 1.41 1.41L19 6.41V10h2V3h-7z\"/>\n            </svg>\n        Previous Website\n            Visit the original SATU Presidents\' Forum website hosted by\n            National Cheng Kung University (NCKU), Taiwan for archives,\n            past events, and historical records.\n        Visit\n    </a>\n</section>				\n			<article>\n									<h3>\n						<a href=\"http://10.18.33.196/index.php/2026/05/18/hello-world/\" rel=\"bookmark\">\n							Hello world!						</a>\n					</h3>\n						Welcome to WordPress. This is your first post. Edit or delete it, then start writing!					\n		</article>\n					<style>\n/* ─── Contact Section ────────────────────────────────────── */\n.satu-contact-section {\n    width: 100%;\n    padding: 60px 48px;\n    display: flex;\n    align-items: center;\n    gap: 60px;\n    box-sizing: border-box;\n    background-color: #ffffff;\n}\n/* ─── Left: Text ─────────────────────────────────────────── */\n.satu-contact-text {\n    flex: 1;\n    min-width: 260px;\n}\n.satu-contact-text h2 {\n    font-family: \"Palatino Linotype\", Palatino, Georgia, serif;\n    font-size: 2rem;\n    font-weight: 700;\n    color: #6B1E1E;\n    margin-bottom: 24px;\n    line-height: 1.2;\n}\n.satu-contact-text address {\n    font-style: normal;\n    font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\n    font-size: 0.95rem;\n    color: #444444;\n    line-height: 2;\n}\n.satu-contact-text address a {\n    color: #6B1E1E;\n    text-decoration: none;\n}\n.satu-contact-text address a:hover {\n    text-decoration: underline;\n}\n/* ─── Right: Map ─────────────────────────────────────────── */\n.satu-contact-map {\n    flex: 1.2;\n    min-width: 300px;\n    height: 320px;\n    border-radius: 8px;\n    overflow: hidden;\n    box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.12);\n    border: 1px solid #e0e0e0;\n}\n.satu-contact-map iframe {\n    width: 100%;\n    height: 100%;\n    border: none;\n    display: block;\n}\n/* ─── Tablet ─────────────────────────────────────────────── */\n@media (max-width: 900px) {\n    .satu-contact-section {\n        padding: 48px 28px;\n        gap: 40px;\n    }\n}\n/* ─── Mobile ─────────────────────────────────────────────── */\n@media (max-width: 650px) {\n    .satu-contact-section {\n        flex-direction: column;\n        padding: 36px 20px;\n        gap: 28px;\n    }\n    .satu-contact-map {\n        width: 100%;\n        height: 260px;\n    }\n    .satu-contact-text h2 {\n        font-size: 1.6rem;\n    }\n}\n</style>\n<section>\n    <!-- ── Left: Address ── -->\n        <h2>Contact Us</h2>\n        <address>\n            Office of the Dean (International Relations)<br>\n            Indian Institute of Technology Bombay<br>\n            Room 416, 4th Floor,<br>\n            Rahul Bajaj Technology Innovation Centre (RBTIC) Building,<br>\n            Powai, Mumbai – 400076<br>\n            India\n        </address>\n    <!-- ── Right: Google Map (IIT Bombay Main Gate) ── -->\n        <iframe\n            src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d3769.9745765143!2d72.91355!3d19.13326!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x3be7b6f5c2b0e6a7%3A0x6e9f8f9b6f9b6f9b!2sIIT%20Bombay%20Main%20Gate!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sin!4v1620000000000!5m2!1sen!2sin\"\n            allowfullscreen=\"\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            referrerpolicy=\"no-referrer-when-downgrade\"\n            title=\"IIT Bombay Main Gate\">\n        </iframe>\n</section>','Home','','inherit','closed','closed','','23-revision-v1','','','2026-05-20 19:05:24','2026-05-20 19:05:24','',23,'http://10.18.33.196/?p=56',0,'revision','',0),
(57,1,'2026-05-20 19:56:27','2026-05-20 19:56:27','<style>\n/* ─── About SATU Section Menu ────────────────────────────── */\n.satu-page-menu {\n    width: 100%;\n    background-color: #f8f4f0;\n    border-top: 3px solid #6B1E1E;\n    border-bottom: 3px solid #6B1E1E;\n    padding: 0;\n    margin-bottom: 40px;\n    box-sizing: border-box;\n}\n.satu-page-menu ul {\n    list-style: none !important;\n    margin: 0 !important;\n    padding: 0 !important;\n    display: flex;\n    flex-wrap: wrap;\n    justify-content: center;\n}\n.satu-page-menu ul li {\n    list-style: none !important;\n    margin: 0 !important;\n    padding: 0 !important;\n}\n.satu-page-menu ul li a {\n    display: block;\n    padding: 14px 28px;\n    font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\n    font-size: 0.85rem;\n    font-weight: 600;\n    letter-spacing: 1.2px;\n    text-transform: uppercase;\n    color: #6B1E1E !important;\n    text-decoration: none !important;\n    position: relative;\n    transition: color 0.25s ease, background 0.25s ease;\n}\n.satu-page-menu ul li a::after {\n    content: \'\';\n    position: absolute;\n    bottom: 0;\n    left: 28px;\n    right: 28px;\n    height: 3px;\n    background: #6B1E1E;\n    transform: scaleX(0);\n    transform-origin: center;\n    transition: transform 0.25s ease;\n}\n.satu-page-menu ul li a:hover {\n    color: #4a1414 !important;\n    background-color: rgba(107, 30, 30, 0.06);\n}\n.satu-page-menu ul li a:hover::after {\n    transform: scaleX(1);\n}\n/* ─── Mobile ─────────────────────────────────────────────── */\n@media (max-width: 600px) {\n    .satu-page-menu ul {\n        flex-direction: column;\n    }\n    .satu-page-menu ul li a {\n        padding: 12px 24px;\n        border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(107, 30, 30, 0.12);\n        font-size: 0.82rem;\n    }\n    .satu-page-menu ul li a::after { display: none; }\n}\n</style>\n<nav>\n    <ul>\n        <li><a href=\"#history\">History</a></li>\n        <li><a href=\"#objectives\">Objectives</a></li>\n        <li><a href=\"#organization\">Organization</a></li>\n        <li><a href=\"#membership-guidelines\">Membership Guidelines</a></li>\n    </ul>\n</nav>		<h2>History</h2><p>As the Southeast Asian region has been facing critical challenges in their economic, societal, and political sectors, there has been a need to gather experts and educators to exchange ideas and face shared challenges. The excellence of universities is an important key to enhance a nation\'s competitiveness. Therefore, President Chiang Kao of the National Cheng Kung University (NCKU), Taiwan, together with the Presidents of prestigious universities of Southeast Asian countries initiated the \"Presidents\' Forum of Southeast Asia and Taiwan Universities\" (abbreviated as SATU Presidents\' Forum) in the year 2003.</p><p>This forum provides a venue for academics to share their valuable experiences to improve higher education and international cooperation in the region. The International Secretariat of the SATU Presidents\' Forum, which includes the two subsections named Academic Exchange Subcommittee and Industry Academia Collaboration Subcommittee, has been established at NCKU to coordinate and to promote the related activities.</p><h2>Objectives</h2><p>SATU Presidents\' Forum will be held biennially to achieve the following objectives:</p><ul><li>To strengthen academic cooperation among Taiwan and Southeast and South Asian countries.</li><li>To foster internationalization through academic and cultural exchange and collaboration.</li><li>To promote the quality of education, research and community services.</li><li>To establish exchange programs for our universities\' students, faculty and administrative staff.</li><li>To foster partnerships between industry and academia.</li><li>To facilitate sustainability in economics, society and the environment.</li></ul><h2>Organization</h2><h3>SATU Presidents\' Forum</h3><p><strong>Chairperson:</strong></p><p>Professor Shireesh B. Kedare, Director, Indian Institute of Technology Bombay, India (IITB)</p><p>Professor Milind Atrey, Deputy Director of Academics, Research and Translation, Indian Institute of Technology Bombay, India (IITB)</p><h3>Steering Committee</h3><p>Please refer to <a href=\"/steering-committee\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">the Steering Committee Section</a> for the incumbent Steering Committee Members.</p><h3>International Secretariat</h3><p><strong>Secretary General:</strong></p><p>Professor Sudarshan Kumar, Dean International Relations, IITB</p><p><strong>Executive Secretary:</strong></p><p>Ms. Rebecca Jadin, Project Manager, Office of International Relations, IITB</p><h2>Membership Guidelines</h2><h3>Eligibility</h3><p>Renowned universities of Southeast and South Asia countries and Taiwan who are interested in the development of enhanced cooperation with other universities in these regions are eligible for membership in the SATU Presidents\' Forum.</p><h3>To Join SATU</h3><p>Send the request for membership in SATU to the International Secretariat. The annual Steering Committee meeting has full and final discretion to decide whether to admit a new member. Admission is approved upon the consent of a majority of the Steering Committee members. When matters of necessity arise, the Committee can make decisions by voting through the circulation of a formal document.</p><h3>Term of Membership</h3><p>Membership in SATU is biennial in its cycle, requiring the payment of dues every other year. The membership term starts on August 1 of the year of membership renewal and expires on July 31 of the following year. For members admitted starting from the second year of a regular biennial membership period (even-numbered years), the membership term starts on August 1 of the admission year and expires on July 31 of the same year.</p><h3>Membership Fee</h3><p>The biennial membership fee is USD 600. If a member is admitted starting from the second year of a regular biennial membership period (even-numbered years), a pro rata membership fee of the member concerned for the first year is USD 300, and then USD 600 when the new biennial membership cycle begins. The International Secretariat will send notifications of membership dues biennially. The payment of the biennial dues shall constitute formal recognition of membership. The payment notice and reminders would be sent to members according to the following schedule:</p><table><thead><tr><th>Month</th><th>Action</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>August</td><td>Issuance of the membership fee payment notice</td></tr><tr><td>End of September</td><td>Issuance of the first membership fee payment reminder</td></tr><tr><td>January</td><td>Final deadline for membership fee payment</td></tr></tbody></table><h3>Membership Benefits</h3><ul><li>Membership benefits include voting in elections at the General Assembly or voting through correspondence.</li><li>Members of SATU are entitled to be elected to serve on the Steering Committee.</li><li>Members can participate in activities held by SATU without registration charges, including the SATU Intensive Program, Joint Research Scheme, fellowship programs, and so forth. Some activities are open to members only.</li><li>Travel expenses and/or accommodations for the participation of SATU members in General Assembly and Steering Committee Meeting will be partly covered.</li><li>Various forms of support will be offered to member university scholars who participate in major SATU events.</li><li>With the consensus among Steering Committee members, the SATU International Secretariat will conduct surveys on academic information/activities of member universities, and circulate the findings among member and observer universities.</li></ul>','About SATU','','publish','closed','closed','','about-satu','','','2026-05-20 20:13:53','2026-05-20 20:13:53','',0,'http://10.18.33.196/?page_id=57',0,'page','',0),
