(70,1,'2026-05-20 20:23:15','2026-05-20 20:23:15','/* ─── About SATU Page Content ────────────────────────────── */\n.satu-page-content {\n    max-width: 900px;\n    margin: 0 auto;\n    padding: 0 24px 60px;\n    font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\n    color: #333333;\n    line-height: 1.8;\n}\n\n.satu-section {\n    margin-bottom: 56px;\n    scroll-margin-top: 80px;\n}\n\n.satu-section h2 {\n    font-family: \"Palatino Linotype\", Palatino, Georgia, serif;\n    font-size: 1.7rem;\n    font-weight: 700;\n    color: #6B1E1E;\n    margin-bottom: 20px;\n    padding-bottom: 10px;\n    border-bottom: 2px solid #c8a96e;\n}\n\n.satu-section p {\n    font-size: 0.95rem;\n    margin-bottom: 14px;\n    color: #444444;\n}\n\n.satu-section ul {\n    padding-left: 24px;\n    margin-bottom: 14px;\n}\n\n.satu-section ul li {\n    font-size: 0.95rem;\n    color: #444444;\n    margin-bottom: 8px;\n    line-height: 1.7;\n}\n\n.satu-section .satu-subsection {\n    margin-top: 28px;\n    margin-bottom: 20px;\n}\n\n.satu-section .satu-subsection h3 {\n    font-family: \"Palatino Linotype\", Palatino, Georgia, serif;\n    font-size: 1.15rem;\n    font-weight: 700;\n    color: #4a1414;\n    margin-bottom: 10px;\n}\n\n.satu-section a {\n    color: #6B1E1E;\n    text-decoration: underline;\n}\n\n.satu-section a:hover {\n    color: #4a1414;\n}\n\n/* ─── Membership Table ───────────────────────────────────── */\n.satu-mem-table {\n    width: 100%;\n    border-collapse: collapse;\n    margin-top: 16px;\n    margin-bottom: 24px;\n    font-size: 0.90rem;\n}\n\n.satu-mem-table th,\n.satu-mem-table td {\n    border: 1px solid #d0c0b0;\n    padding: 12px 16px;\n    text-align: left;\n    vertical-align: top;\n    color: #444444;\n}\n\n.satu-mem-table th {\n    background-color: #6B1E1E;\n    color: #ffffff;\n    font-weight: 600;\n    letter-spacing: 0.5px;\n}\n\n.satu-mem-table tr:nth-child(even) td {\n    background-color: #f9f4f0;\n}\n\n/* ─── Mobile ─────────────────────────────────────────────── */\n@media (max-width: 600px) {\n    .satu-page-menu ul { flex-direction: column; }\n    .satu-page-menu ul li a {\n        padding: 12px 24px;\n        border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(107, 30, 30, 0.12);\n        font-size: 0.82rem;\n    }\n    .satu-page-menu ul li a::after { display: none; }\n}\n\n\n/* ─── Constitution Page ──────────────────────────────────── */\n.satu-constitution {\n    max-width: 860px;\n    margin: 0 auto;\n    padding: 40px 24px 60px;\n    font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\n    color: #333333;\n    line-height: 1.8;\n}\n\n.satu-constitution .satu-const-header {\n    text-align: center;\n    margin-bottom: 32px;\n    padding-bottom: 24px;\n    border-bottom: 2px solid #c8a96e;\n}\n\n.satu-constitution .satu-const-header h1 {\n    font-family: \"Palatino Linotype\", Palatino, Georgia, serif;\n    font-size: 1.15rem;\n    font-weight: 700;\n    color: #6B1E1E;\n    line-height: 1.6;\n    margin-bottom: 16px;\n    text-transform: uppercase;\n    letter-spacing: 1px;\n}\n\n.satu-constitution .satu-const-amendments {\n    text-align: right;\n    font-size: 0.85rem;\n    color: #666666;\n    line-height: 2;\n    font-style: italic;\n}\n\n.satu-constitution .satu-const-article {\n    margin-bottom: 40px;\n}\n\n.satu-constitution .satu-const-article h2 {\n    font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\n    font-size: 0.95rem;\n    font-weight: 700;\n    color: #6B1E1E;\n    text-transform: uppercase;\n    letter-spacing: 1px;\n    margin-bottom: 14px;\n    padding-bottom: 8px;\n    border-bottom: 1px solid #c8a96e;\n}\n\n.satu-constitution .satu-const-article p {\n    font-size: 0.92rem;\n    color: #444444;\n    margin-bottom: 12px;\n}\n\n.satu-constitution ol {\n    padding-left: 24px;\n    margin-bottom: 14px;\n}\n\n.satu-constitution ol li {\n    font-size: 0.92rem;\n    color: #444444;\n    margin-bottom: 10px;\n    line-height: 1.75;\n    padding-left: 6px;\n}\n\n.satu-constitution ul {\n    padding-left: 24px;\n    margin-bottom: 10px;\n    margin-top: 8px;\n}\n\n.satu-constitution ul li {\n    font-size: 0.92rem;\n    color: #444444;\n    margin-bottom: 6px;\n    line-height: 1.75;\n    list-style-type: disc;\n}\n\n.satu-constitution ul ul {\n    margin-top: 6px;\n    padding-left: 24px;\n}\n\n.satu-constitution ul ul li {\n    list-style-type: circle;\n}\n\n.satu-constitution strong {\n    color: #333333;\n}\n\n@media (max-width: 600px) {\n    .satu-constitution { padding: 24px 16px 40px; }\n    .satu-constitution .satu-const-header h1 { font-size: 1rem; }\n}','hello-elementor-child-satu','','inherit','closed','closed','','63-revision-v1','','','2026-05-20 20:23:15','2026-05-20 20:23:15','',63,'http://10.18.33.196/?p=70',0,'revision','',0),
(71,1,'2026-05-20 20:23:34','2026-05-20 20:23:34','<!-- Header -->\n<h1>\nPresidents\' Forum of<br>\nSoutheast and South Asia and Taiwan Universities<br>\n(SATU Presidents\' Forum)\n</h1>\n2007<br>\nAmended on November 12, 2009<br>\nAmended on October 31, 2012<br>\nAmended on November 24, 2021\n<!-- Article I -->\n<h2>Article I: Name</h2>\n<p>The organization is officially named \"Presidents\' Forum of Southeast and South Asia and Taiwan Universities,\" abbreviated as \"SATU Presidents\' Forum.\"</p>\n<!-- Article II -->\n<h2>Article II: Objectives</h2>\n<p>The objectives of the SATU Presidents\' Forum are:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>To strengthen academic cooperation among Taiwan and Southeast and South Asian countries</li>\n<li>To foster internationalization through academic and cultural exchange and collaboration</li>\n<li>To promote the quality of education, research and community services</li>\n<li>To establish exchange programs for our universities\' students, faculty and administrative staff</li>\n<li>To foster partnerships between industry and academia</li>\n<li>To facilitate sustainability in economics, society and the environment</li>\n</ol>\n<!-- Article III -->\n<h2>Article III: Organization</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<strong>Forum</strong><br>\nThe Forum, with its objectives described in Article II, is chaired by the President of National Cheng Kung University (NCKU), Taiwan.\n</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Steering Committee</strong><br>\nThe Steering Committee provides leadership and guidance for the Forum. Members of the Steering Committee are elected by member universities or appointed by the SATU Chair and serve a two-year renewable term. The Chairperson of the Forum also serves as the Chair of the Steering Committee.\n</li>\n<li>\n<strong>International Secretariat</strong><br>\nThe International Secretariat, headed by the Secretary General and located at NCKU, runs the affairs of the Forum under the direction of the Chairperson and the Steering Committee. The International Secretariat is responsible for the internal and external communications of the Forum. The Executive Vice-President of NCKU acts as the Secretary General.\n</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- Article IV -->\n<h2>Article IV: Membership</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Starting members include those universities that attended the 2003 \"Presidents\' Forum of Southeast Asia Universities.\"</li>\n<li>Additional members are to be nominated and approved by the members of the Steering Committee.</li>\n<li>\nCriteria of membership:\n<ul>\n<li>Comprehensive university</li>\n<li>Technological and vocational institution with a high reputation and distinguished performance</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Maintenance of membership: To support the development and efforts of the SATU Presidents\' Forum, a membership fee of USD 600 is due biennially to maintain membership. Each member will receive a biennial notice concerning when its membership is due to expire, specifying the means by which its membership can be renewed and the appropriate membership fee. If a member is admitted starting from the second year of a regular biennial membership period (even-numbered years), a pro rata membership fee of USD 300 will be due to cover the remaining year of the membership period concerned. The membership fee for the member will be USD 600 starting from the next regular biennial membership period. The membership fee collection and notification will be administered by the International Secretariat.</li>\n</ol>\n<!-- Article V -->\n<h2>Article V: Forum</h2>\n<p>The Forum will be held biennially. Presidents of member universities are invited to attend. The host university and topics of the Forum are to be decided in the meeting of the Steering Committee. In the Forum, member universities also elect a new Steering Committee for the next tenancy.</p>\n<!-- Article VI -->\n<h2>Article VI: Steering Committee</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>In addition to the National Cheng Kung University, the permanent Chair member, the Steering Committee shall be composed of a maximum of two Presidents from each member country. In the case of countries where there is only one member university, there shall only be one representative. The Steering Committee reviews the implementation of every agenda and program, and initiates a new two-year calendar of events. A meeting of the Steering Committee will be held annually.</li>\n<li>Steering Committee members will hold their seats for a two-year term.</li>\n<li>The first member university of a country shall be elected by representatives from that country. The election shall occur during the General Assembly. Each voter shall write in two names. The university with the highest number of votes shall become the first member, provided the university accepts.</li>\n<li>The second member university of a country shall be appointed by the SATU Chair.</li>\n<li>Motions must be carried by at least two-thirds vote of the Steering Committee members.</li>\n</ol>\n<!-- Article VII -->\n<h2>Article VII: International Secretariat</h2>\n<p>Two sections are set up under the International Secretariat, namely the Academic Exchange and Industry–Academia Collaborations, respectively. The duties of the International Secretariat and each section are described as follows:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<strong>International Secretariat</strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Managing external communications</li>\n<li>Updating and maintaining websites of the Forum</li>\n<li>Arranging annual meetings, and the biennial SATU Presidents\' Forum</li>\n<li>Publishing annual reports</li>\n<li>Drafter the Forum\'s calendar of events</li>\n<li>Raising funds and integrating resources</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Academic Exchange</strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Initiating bilateral academic agreements between member universities</li>\n<li>Coordinating and arranging joint research projects</li>\n<li>Arranging faculty and student exchange programs</li>\n<li>Arranging student seminars and activities</li>\n<li>Coordinating and arranging short-term visits for students</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Industry–Academia Collaboration</strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Coordinating industrial–academic cooperation projects</li>\n<li>Arranging industrial–academic workshops</li>\n<li>Coordinating and arranging student training programs</li>\n<li>Arranging two-way visits for industry and member universities</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- Article VIII -->\n<h2>Article VIII: Amendment</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Interpretation of the Constitution should be addressed by the Steering Committee.</li>\n<li>The Constitution may be adopted, annulled, or amended by the affirmative votes of a majority of the member universities at the General Assembly of a Biennial Forum. Once the motion is passed and announced in the General Assembly, the changes are effective immediately.</li>\n<li>\nNo such action shall be taken at the General Assembly of a Biennial Forum unless the change in the Constitution is proposed as follows:\n<ul>\n<li>By the Steering Committee</li>\n<li>By the Steering Committee as a consequence of an official letter cast by one-third of the active members a month in advance</li>\n<li>By written request of two-thirds of the active members at the General Assembly of a Biennial Forum</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ol>','Constitution','','publish','closed','closed','','constitution','','','2026-05-20 20:24:40','2026-05-20 20:24:40','',0,'http://10.18.33.196/?page_id=71',0,'page','',0),
