(96,1,'2026-05-20 21:31:22','2026-05-20 21:31:22','<h2 \n		data-interaction-id=\"f5d366f\" \n		class=\"e-heading-base\" \n	>\n			About General Assembly\n		</h2>\n		<p>General Assembly meetings are held biennially. The next General Assembly meeting will be held in 2027. More details to follow.</p>					<h2 \n		data-interaction-id=\"6dc315f\" \n		class=\"e-heading-base\" \n	>\n			Previous Events\n		</h2>\n		[table id=1 /]<p><em>For more information, please refer to <a href=\"https://satu.ncku.edu.tw/p/412-1036-1789.php?Lang=en\">satu.ncku.edu.tw</a></em></p>','General Assembly','','inherit','closed','closed','','92-revision-v1','','','2026-05-20 21:31:22','2026-05-20 21:31:22','',92,'http://10.18.33.196/?p=96',0,'revision','',0),
(97,1,'2026-05-20 21:37:41','2026-05-20 21:37:41','<h2 \n		data-interaction-id=\"35b5170\" \n		class=\"e-heading-base\" \n	>\n			Activities\n		</h2>\n		<p><b>Joint Research Scheme (JRS)</b></p><ul><li aria-level=\"1\">About the SATU Joint Research Scheme (JRS)<ul><li aria-level=\"2\">The SATU Presidents\' Forum International Secretariat launched the SATU Joint Research Scheme (or SATU JRS) in 2012 to provide a collaborative platform that facilitates academic research cooperation among SATU member universities. It serves as a matching platform where scholars from different SATU member universities can connect with like-minded researchers and form research collaborations together. </li><li aria-level=\"2\">The JRS platform does not provide funding for the matched projects. Each host university may provide funding or alternative types of support to implement the matched project.</li></ul></li><li aria-level=\"1\">Aim<ul><li aria-level=\"2\">The SATU Presidents\' Forum International Secretariat works as a networking platform to connect scholars who share similar research interests. The aim of JRS is to help integrate resources to increase the quality, quantity and global scope of the research being conducted at our member universities, with the goal of advancing the research achievements of the SATU community.</li></ul></li><li aria-level=\"1\">Eligibility<ul><li aria-level=\"2\">Investigators must be working at one of the <a href=\"/members\">SATU member universities</a> throughout the entire JRS process and have a doctoral degree. </li></ul></li><li aria-level=\"1\">Topics<ul><li aria-level=\"2\">Acceptable topics include those involving Liberal Arts, Management, Sciences, Social Sciences, Engineering, Electrical Engineering &amp; Computer Science, Planning &amp; Design, Bioscience &amp; Biotechnology, and Medicine in Southeast and South Asia, and multidisciplinary research. Each project consists of a team of researchers, including a Principal Investigator (PI) and Co-Principal Investigator(s) (Co-PI(s)) from SATU member universities.</li></ul></li><li aria-level=\"1\">Timeline<ul><li aria-level=\"2\">April 6-27, 2026</li></ul></li><li aria-level=\"1\">Stage 1<ul><li aria-level=\"2\">Call for PI Proposals<ul><li aria-level=\"3\">Online submission</li></ul></li><li aria-level=\"2\">PI(s) as project host</li><li aria-level=\"2\">May 4-25, 2026</li></ul></li><li aria-level=\"1\">Stage 2<ul><li aria-level=\"2\">Call for Co-PI(s)<ul><li aria-level=\"3\">Online application</li></ul></li><li aria-level=\"2\">To participate in projects hosted by PI(s) of other universities</li><li aria-level=\"2\">June 8-22, 2026</li></ul></li><li aria-level=\"1\">Stage 3<ul><li aria-level=\"2\">Project Matching<ul><li aria-level=\"3\">Co-PI applications to be reviewed by PI(s)</li></ul></li><li aria-level=\"2\">July 6, 2026</li></ul></li><li aria-level=\"1\">Announcement<ul><li aria-level=\"2\">Matching results</li></ul></li><li aria-level=\"1\">Projects can start</li><li aria-level=\"1\">Matching Procedures<ul><li aria-level=\"2\">The PI projects and the Co-PI applications will be matched as follows:<ul><li aria-level=\"3\">1. Call for PI proposals<br />In this stage, all academic members of SATU member universities are invited to submit their research project proposals via the PI proposal submission forms. At the end of this stage, the project information will be compiled into a PI project list.</li><li aria-level=\"3\">2. Call for Co-PI applications<br />All academic members of SATU member universities can refer to the PI project list for projects which they would like to join as Co-PIs, and submit the Co-PI application form, in which they will be asked to indicate the code of the projects of interest, and provide a CV.</li><li aria-level=\"3\">3. Matching - Co-PI application sent to PI for review and selection<br />When the Co-PI application period is over, each PI will receive a list of Co-PI applicants interested in joining his/her project. The PI will then be asked to review the Co-PIs\' applications, and inform us of the Co-PI(s) s/he would like to work with.</li><li aria-level=\"3\">4. Matching announcement<br />Upon receipt of the PIs\' decisions, we will notify both the PIs and Co-PIs if the matching is successful. If the matching is successful, the PI and Co-PIs concerned will be provided with the contact information of all investigators in their respective teams.<br />This is the point where the JRS matching exercise completes. The PIs and Co-PIs can then start their own discussions on research planning and implementation etc.</li></ul></li><li aria-level=\"2\">A list of matched projects will also be released on this website.</li></ul></li><li aria-level=\"1\">Application<ul><li aria-level=\"2\">Interested scholars can join the JRS as Principal Investigator (PI) and/or Co-Principal Investigator. </li><li aria-level=\"2\">As Principal Investigators (PI)<ul><li aria-level=\"3\">To join the JRS as a Principal Investigator (PI), please submit your research proposal via the \"PI Proposal\" Form below.</li><li aria-level=\"3\">Information needed when submitting the research proposal<ul><li aria-level=\"4\">PIs personal and contact information</li><li aria-level=\"4\">Project field</li><li aria-level=\"4\">The project’s related UN Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs)<ul><li aria-level=\"5\">Further information about UN SDGs (<a href=\"https://sdgs.un.org/goals\">https://sdgs.un.org/goals)</a></li></ul></li><li aria-level=\"4\">Project title</li><li aria-level=\"4\">Project description (plain text)</li></ul></li></ul></li><li aria-level=\"2\">As Co-Principal Investigators (Co-PI)<ul><li aria-level=\"3\">The application as Co-Principal Investigator (Co-PI) will be open after the PI proposal submission period is closed.</li><li aria-level=\"3\">Things to do before filling in Co-PIs application<ul><li aria-level=\"4\">Refer to the PI project list (to be available in due course on this webpage) for the code(s) of the preferred project(s). You will need to choose the code when filling in the application.</li><li aria-level=\"4\">Prepare a CV, complete with your publications:<ul><li aria-level=\"5\">All papers or works published in the last five years, including articles published in periodicals, books, conference papers, and technical reports.</li><li aria-level=\"5\">List these papers and works in order of publication date (latest publication on top).</li></ul></li></ul></li><li aria-level=\"3\">The application along with the CV will be sent to PI for review.</li></ul></li></ul></li><li aria-level=\"1\">JRS Funding Schemes<ul><li aria-level=\"2\">The JRS platform does not provide funding for the matched projects. However, a number of SATU member universities provide financial support for their host projects. </li><li aria-level=\"2\">Please check with your institution’s international relations / research office for the availability of any funding opportunities.</li></ul></li></ul><p><b>International Summer School</b></p><ul><li aria-level=\"1\">IIT Bombay will be hosting the 2026 International Summer School. It will be conducted in-person from July 6-10, 2026. This program offers a diverse range of courses delivered by IIT Bombay\'s expert faculty, catering to undergraduate, postgraduate, and PhD students - <b>exclusively for students of foreign origin.</b></li><li aria-level=\"1\">We welcome 2 nominations from your esteemed institute to apply for this opportunity. Please notify <em>satu[at]iitb.ac.in </em>of the nominated students by <b>April 13, 2026</b>. The deadline for students to complete the application will be on <b>April 20, 2026</b>. </li><li aria-level=\"1\">SATU will provide coverage for the registration/participation fee of the program. Please note that students will be responsible for airfare, visa processing fees, and local transportation to IIT Bombay. </li><li aria-level=\"1\">IIT Bombay is able to welcome a total of 20 students for this opportunity. If there is a strong interest in participating, there is a possibility that the number may be increased. Please note that the 20 students will be chosen as per the date of the completion of the application.</li></ul><p><b>JRS Webinars</b></p><ul><li aria-level=\"1\">To be announced at a later date</li></ul><p><b>Local Chapter Meets</b></p><ul><li aria-level=\"1\">To be announced at a later date</li></ul>','Activities','','publish','closed','closed','','activities','','','2026-05-22 09:34:17','2026-05-22 09:34:17','',0,'http://10.18.33.196/?page_id=97',0,'page','',0),
(98,1,'2026-05-20 21:34:07','2026-05-20 21:34:07','','Activities','','inherit','closed','closed','','97-revision-v1','','','2026-05-20 21:34:07','2026-05-20 21:34:07','',97,'http://10.18.33.196/?p=98',0,'revision','',0),
