ike to work with.</li><li aria-level=\"3\">4. Matching announcement<br />Upon receipt of the PIs\' decisions, we will notify both the PIs and Co-PIs if the matching is successful. If the matching is successful, the PI and Co-PIs concerned will be provided with the contact information of all investigators in their respective teams.<br />This is the point where the JRS matching exercise completes. The PIs and Co-PIs can then start their own discussions on research planning and implementation etc.</li></ul></li><li aria-level=\"2\">A list of matched projects will also be released on this website.</li></ul></li><li aria-level=\"1\">Application<ul><li aria-level=\"2\">Interested scholars can join the JRS as Principal Investigator (PI) and/or Co-Principal Investigator. </li><li aria-level=\"2\">As Principal Investigators (PI)<ul><li aria-level=\"3\">To join the JRS as a Principal Investigator (PI), please submit your research proposal via the \"PI Proposal\" Form below.</li><li aria-level=\"3\">Information needed when submitting the research proposal<ul><li aria-level=\"4\">PIs personal and contact information</li><li aria-level=\"4\">Project field</li><li aria-level=\"4\">The project’s related UN Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs)<ul><li aria-level=\"5\">Further information about UN SDGs (<a href=\"https://sdgs.un.org/goals\">https://sdgs.un.org/goals)</a></li></ul></li><li aria-level=\"4\">Project title</li><li aria-level=\"4\">Project description (plain text)</li></ul></li></ul></li><li aria-level=\"2\">As Co-Principal Investigators (Co-PI)<ul><li aria-level=\"3\">The application as Co-Principal Investigator (Co-PI) will be open after the PI proposal submission period is closed.</li><li aria-level=\"3\">Things to do before filling in Co-PIs application<ul><li aria-level=\"4\">Refer to the PI project list (to be available in due course on this webpage) for the code(s) of the preferred project(s). You will need to choose the code when filling in the application.</li><li aria-level=\"4\">Prepare a CV, complete with your publications:<ul><li aria-level=\"5\">All papers or works published in the last five years, including articles published in periodicals, books, conference papers, and technical reports.</li><li aria-level=\"5\">List these papers and works in order of publication date (latest publication on top).</li></ul></li></ul></li><li aria-level=\"3\">The application along with the CV will be sent to PI for review.</li></ul></li></ul></li><li aria-level=\"1\">JRS Funding Schemes<ul><li aria-level=\"2\">The JRS platform does not provide funding for the matched projects. However, a number of SATU member universities provide financial support for their host projects. </li><li aria-level=\"2\">Please check with your institution’s international relations / research office for the availability of any funding opportunities.</li></ul></li></ul><p><b>International Summer School</b></p><ul><li aria-level=\"1\">IIT Bombay will be hosting the 2026 International Summer School. It will be conducted in-person from July 6-10, 2026. This program offers a diverse range of courses delivered by IIT Bombay\'s expert faculty, catering to undergraduate, postgraduate, and PhD students - <b>exclusively for students of foreign origin.</b></li><li aria-level=\"1\">We welcome 2 nominations from your esteemed institute to apply for this opportunity. Please notify <em>satu[at]iitb.ac.in </em>of the nominated students by <b>April 13, 2026</b>. The deadline for students to complete the application will be on <b>April 20, 2026</b>. </li><li aria-level=\"1\">SATU will provide coverage for the registration/participation fee of the program. Please note that students will be responsible for airfare, visa processing fees, and local transportation to IIT Bombay. </li><li aria-level=\"1\">IIT Bombay is able to welcome a total of 20 students for this opportunity. If there is a strong interest in participating, there is a possibility that the number may be increased. Please note that the 20 students will be chosen as per the date of the completion of the application.</li></ul><p><b>JRS Webinars</b></p><ul><li aria-level=\"1\">To be announced at a later date</li></ul><p><b>Local Chapter Meets</b></p><ul><li aria-level=\"1\">To be announced at a later date</li></ul><p> </p>','Activities','','inherit','closed','closed','','97-revision-v1','','','2026-05-20 21:38:39','2026-05-20 21:38:39','',97,'http://10.18.33.196/?p=101',0,'revision','',0),
(102,1,'2026-05-20 21:39:33','2026-05-20 21:39:33','<h2 \n		data-interaction-id=\"38f148b\" \n		class=\"e-heading-base\" \n	>\n			SATU  Member Application\n		</h2>\n		<p>If your university is interested in becoming a member in the SATU Presidents’ Forum, please fill out the below form and send it to the International Secretariat at <em>satu[at]iitb.ac.in</em>. <br /><br />The Steering Committee will review the application at the annual meeting. Admission is approved upon the consent of a majority of the members. When matters of necessity arise, the Steering Committee can make decisions by voting through the circulation of a formal document.</p><p>(LINK TO THE APPLICATION)</p><p>For more information regarding the membership, see the section on <a href=\"/about-satu/#membership-guidelines\">Membership Guidelines.</a></p>','Member Application','','publish','closed','closed','','member-application','','','2026-05-20 21:43:51','2026-05-20 21:43:51','',0,'http://10.18.33.196/?page_id=102',0,'page','',0),
